    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:1.1",
          "pli": "Evaṃ me sutaṃ. ",
          "en": "So I have heard. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:1.2",
          "pli": "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. ",
          "en": "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:1.3",
          "pli": "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: ",
          "en": "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:1.4",
          "pli": "“bhikkhavo”ti. ",
          "en": "“Mendicants!” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:1.5",
          "pli": "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. ",
          "en": "“Venerable sir,” they replied. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:1.6",
          "pli": "Bhagavā etadavoca: ",
          "en": "The Buddha said this: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:2.1",
          "pli": "“Cakkhuṃ, bhikkhave, aniccaṃ. ",
          "en": "“Mendicants, the eye is impermanent. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:2.2",
          "pli": "Yadaniccaṃ taṃ dukkhaṃ; ",
          "en": "What’s impermanent is suffering. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:2.3",
          "pli": "yaṃ dukkhaṃ tadanattā. ",
          "en": "What’s suffering is not-self. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:2.4",
          "pli": "Yadanattā taṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ. ",
          "en": "And what’s not-self should be truly seen with right understanding like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’ "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:2.5",
          "pli": "Sotaṃ aniccaṃ. ",
          "en": "The ear is impermanent. … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:2.6",
          "pli": "Yadaniccaṃ … pe … ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:2.7",
          "pli": "ghānaṃ aniccaṃ. ",
          "en": "The nose is impermanent. … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:2.8",
          "pli": "Yadaniccaṃ … pe … ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:2.9",
          "pli": "jivhā aniccā. ",
          "en": "The tongue is impermanent. … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:2.10",
          "pli": "Yadaniccaṃ taṃ dukkhaṃ; ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:2.11",
          "pli": "yaṃ dukkhaṃ tadanattā. ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:2.12",
          "pli": "Yadanattā taṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ. ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:2.13",
          "pli": "Kāyo anicco. ",
          "en": "The body is impermanent. … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:2.14",
          "pli": "Yadaniccaṃ … pe … ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:2.15",
          "pli": "mano anicco. ",
          "en": "The mind is impermanent. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:2.16",
          "pli": "Yadaniccaṃ taṃ dukkhaṃ; ",
          "en": "What’s impermanent is suffering. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:2.17",
          "pli": "yaṃ dukkhaṃ tadanattā. ",
          "en": "What’s suffering is not-self. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:2.18",
          "pli": "Yadanattā taṃ ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ. ",
          "en": "And what’s not-self should be truly seen with right understanding like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’ "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:2.19",
          "pli": "Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako cakkhusmimpi nibbindati, sotasmimpi nibbindati, ghānasmimpi nibbindati, jivhāyapi nibbindati, kāyasmimpi nibbindati, manasmimpi nibbindati. ",
          "en": "Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with the eye, ear, nose, tongue, body, and mind. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:2.20",
          "pli": "Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati; vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti. ",
          "en": "Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:2.21",
          "pli": "‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānātī”ti. ",
          "en": "They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.1:2.22",
          "pli": "Paṭhamaṃ. ",
          "en": ""
        }
      ],
